<TITLE> Robbery, rape at Baptist Mission in Gopalganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, Jan 6 (bdnews24.com)  Unidentified gunmen on Monday night raped the wife of a Baptist priest during a robbery at a Baptist Christian Mission in Gopalganj. "A group of gunmen looted the church and sexually assaulted the wife of its cleric Shankar Hazra," Mohammad Liakat Ali Khan, officer in charge of the local police station, told reporters. Khan said they had already arrested two suspects Ilyas Mridha (50) and Sunil Barai (40) for the assault at church in Noyakandi Chakshin under Muksudpur upazila. Hazra's wife was admitted to the upazila health centre and then transferred to Gopalganj Hospital after her condition deteriorated, he added. Hazra's wife told reporters: "A gang of 8/9 gunmen stormed our room and tied my husband's hands and legs and then violated me at gun point." Khan said robbers robbed them of a television set, a CD player, a mobile phone, cash and golden ornaments. Two separate cases were filed with the police. bdnews24.co
